-- U.A.E. RAK Airways to Restart Operations This Year After Flight Suspension
-- Shaji Mathew
-- 2010-06-30T06:57:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/u-a-e-rak-airways-to-restart-operations-this-year-after-flight-suspension.html

          
          
             RAK Airways PJSC, the United Arab
Emiratesâ€™ airline owned by the emirate of Ras al-Khaimah, plans
to restart operations before the end of this year after
suspending flights for about a year.  
 The suspension was because of the global financial crisis,
the airline said in an e-mailed statement today. The company is
looking at destinations in the Gulf, Africa and the Indian
Subcontinent, it said.  
 Ras al-Khaimah is one of the seven members of the U.A.E.  
